# Megaplan

When the user asks to "megaplan this" or the task is high-risk/multi-stage,
route the work through the `megaplan` CLI before making code changes.

## Start

Before running `init`, ask the user:
- Execution mode: `auto-approve` or `review` (default)
- Robustness: `light`, `standard` (default), or `thorough`

```bash
megaplan init --project-dir "$PROJECT_DIR" [--auto-approve] [--robustness light|standard|thorough] "$IDEA"
```

## Workflow

Follow the `next_step` field returned by the CLI at each step:

1. `megaplan clarify` — show the refined idea and keep moving unless the user redirects
2. `megaplan plan` — show the plan summary and keep moving
3. `megaplan critique` — surface concrete flags; call out scope creep explicitly if it appears
4. `megaplan evaluate`
5. If `CONTINUE`: `megaplan integrate`, then loop back to critique
6. If `SKIP`: `megaplan gate`
7. If `ESCALATE`/`ABORT`: present to user, use `megaplan override ...` only if they choose to bypass
8. After gate:
   - Auto-approve: `megaplan execute --confirm-destructive`
   - Review: summarize the plan, offer to read `.megaplan/plans/<name>/final.md` inline, then run `megaplan execute --confirm-destructive --user-approved` only after explicit approval
9. `megaplan review` — verify success criteria

Default behavior is to keep moving while showing intermediate results. Review mode pauses only at the gate → execute checkpoint.

## Useful Commands

```bash
megaplan status --plan <name>
megaplan audit --plan <name>
megaplan list
megaplan override add-note --plan <name> "context"
megaplan override abort --plan <name>
```
